Description: Fragment of round handle from a Brindisi pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine buff. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Latin inscription.
Curator's comments: Name C(h)ariton. cf. Desy, Ph., Les timbres amphoriques de l'Apulie republicaine (Oxford 1989) 173. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 201, 19. D. Manacorda and S. Pallecchi, Le fornace romane di Giancola (Bari, 2012) 310 (not same die).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1284)
